WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:04.400
<i>This program is suitable
for viewers ages 15 and up.</i>

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:01:25.400 --> 00:01:27.500
Anna! Wake up!

4
00:01:27.500 --> 00:01:29.290
Anna! Anna!

5
00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:32.960
<i>No. Anna!</i>

6
00:01:32.960 --> 00:01:35.100
<i>Please don't die!</i>

7
00:01:35.690 --> 00:01:37.800
<i>Please don't die!</i>

8
00:01:42.690 --> 00:01:44.990
Wake up. Anna! Anna!

9
00:01:44.990 --> 00:01:46.490
Wake up. Anna!

10
00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:02.600
What? 911?

11
00:02:02.600 --> 00:02:05.400
Are you crazy?
You can't call 911!

12
00:02:05.990 --> 00:02:09.400
But sir. the JSS ambulance
will take far too long!

13
00:02:09.400 --> 00:02:10.400
We have no time!

14
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:14.190
You can't! I'll cancel the call to 911
and send over one of our ambulances.

15
00:02:14.190 --> 00:02:15.990
Sir! Sir!

16
00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:19.100
Damn it!

17
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:23.690
Chief! The situation is
looking quite bad!

18
00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:24.690
Wait for me!

19
00:02:25.400 --> 00:02:27.190
<i>[NO CARS ALLOWED]</i>

20
00:02:27.190 --> 00:02:28.690
- Floor it.
- Yes. sir?

21
00:02:28.690 --> 00:02:30.990
- I said floor it. bastard!
- Yes. sir.

22
00:02:41.990 --> 00:02:44.590
Are you coming to. Anna?
Huh? Anna!

23
00:02:44.590 --> 00:02:45.700
Anna!

24
00:02:47.490 --> 00:02:50.990
Hey. what are you doing?
Why isn't the ambulance coming?

25
00:02:50.990 --> 00:02:52.900
Damn it. this is
driving me crazy!

26
00:03:00.990 --> 00:03:02.490
Get her in!
Quickly!

27
00:03:02.490 --> 00:03:03.930
Hurry!

28
00:03:03.940 --> 00:03:05.400
Move.

29
00:03:11.790 --> 00:03:14.090
Move.
Move. punk!

30
00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:41.700
This is K2.
Heading toward the nearest hospital.

31
00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:43.300
You can't go to a hospital.

32
00:03:43.300 --> 00:03:45.400
- Head to the JSS Headquarters.
- What?

33
00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:47.090
We're not in a situation
where we can afford to...

34
00:03:47.090 --> 00:03:48.900
Just step on it already!

35
00:03:48.900 --> 00:03:50.090
If we go to the hospital.
we're all dead!

36
00:03:50.090 --> 00:03:51.700
Ugh. damn it!

37
00:04:52.500 --> 00:04:54.500
- Move.
- Out of the way!

38
00:04:58.200 --> 00:04:59.590
Excuse us!

39
00:04:59.590 --> 00:05:00.790
Move. move!

40
00:05:03.090 --> 00:05:06.290
Huh? Why are they all
in such a hurry?

41
00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:14.000
Look at you. acting all pretty!
It's all Photoshop. isn't it?

42
00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:16.090
- No. I didn't!
- Oh. whatever!

43
00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:22.400
She's so pretty.
Where have I seen her before?

44
00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:25.200
What do you mean?
She's sitting right in front of you.

45
00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:28.700
No. not you.
The woman sitting behind you.

46
00:05:28.700 --> 00:05:31.400
I definitely feel like
I've seen this face a lot.

47
00:05:33.550 --> 00:05:34.590
Isn't it that woman?

48
00:05:34.590 --> 00:05:35.590
You know. that "angel"!

49
00:05:35.590 --> 00:05:38.290
The "angel" that
Jean-Paul Lafelt is looking for!

50
00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:41.590
- Well?
- No way. I don't think so.

51
00:05:41.590 --> 00:05:43.090
Why would she be in Korea?

52
00:05:43.090 --> 00:05:44.590
Isn't she in Spain?

53
00:05:45.590 --> 00:05:48.200
I don't think so.
This looks just like her.

54
00:05:49.090 --> 00:05:51.790
Oh. I know.
Let's put this photo on social media.

55
00:05:51.790 --> 00:05:52.790
Okay?

56
00:05:53.590 --> 00:05:59.900
<i>[ISN'T THIS WOMAN THE BARCELONA
ANGEL. BY ANY CHANCE? #LOL]</i>

57
00:06:04.790 --> 00:06:06.590
Please go outside.
Mr. Je Ha.

58
00:06:06.590 --> 00:06:09.700
What?
Oh. Okay.

59
00:06:17.500 --> 00:06:21.090
Leave! You'll only be a hindrance
if you stay here like this!

60
00:06:22.500 --> 00:06:24.090
I understand.

61
00:06:53.900 --> 00:06:56.200
<i>Hey. hurry and take this.
It'll melt.</i>

62
00:06:56.200 --> 00:06:58.700
<i>Your dad told me
to buy this for you.</i>

63
00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:00.590
<i>Really?</i>

64
00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:03.200
<i>Did Dad really tell you
to give this to me?</i>

65
00:07:03.700 --> 00:07:05.400
<i>Of course.</i>

66
00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:07.400
<i>Okay.</i>

67
00:07:09.400 --> 00:07:13.200
<i>If it's from Dad.
I have to eat it.</i>

68
00:07:14.200 --> 00:07:15.700
<i>It's good.</i>

69
00:07:34.200 --> 00:07:35.790
<i>No.</i>

70
00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:38.790
Mom?

71
00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:44.400
<i>No!</i>

72
00:08:07.790 --> 00:08:09.900
M... mom?

73
00:08:38.590 --> 00:08:40.500
Are you all right?

74
00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:42.090
Miss. are you all right?

75
00:08:50.500 --> 00:08:51.790
Please calm down.

76
00:08:54.500 --> 00:08:56.590
Are you experiencing
any pain anywhere?

77
00:09:10.190 --> 00:09:11.400
Where is this place?

78
00:09:11.400 --> 00:09:14.100
This is the medical room
at JSS Headquarters.

79
00:09:14.100 --> 00:09:16.290
Mr. Je Ha brought you
here from the park.

80
00:09:16.290 --> 00:09:19.190
It would've been terrible if he'd been
even a little bit later than he was.

81
00:10:01.500 --> 00:10:03.670
Hey! How did things
go in there?

82
00:10:04.300 --> 00:10:06.190
I've managed to calm down
the allergic reaction quite a bit.

83
00:10:06.690 --> 00:10:09.100
Um. shouldn't we move her
to a hospital now?

84
00:10:09.100 --> 00:10:10.690
I'm a doctor too. you know.

85
00:10:10.690 --> 00:10:14.600
And we're better equipped
here than most ERs.

86
00:10:15.190 --> 00:10:19.690
Her body will be fine with some medicine.
but the issue is her mental state.

87
00:10:19.690 --> 00:10:22.600
I don't know what she'll do again
in her current mental state.

88
00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:26.000
She'll need to see a
psychologist eventually.

89
00:10:26.600 --> 00:10:28.690
You'll have to keep
an especially close watch on her.

90
00:10:32.790 --> 00:10:39.190
But. um... did she say anything about me?
Like. that I harassed her or something?

91
00:10:39.190 --> 00:10:41.190
What kind of nonsense is that?

92
00:10:41.190 --> 00:10:43.690
You think she's in a mental state
to be saying such things?

93
00:10:43.690 --> 00:10:46.900
- Geez!
- Geez.

94
00:10:52.190 --> 00:10:55.100
Why did you send back the ambulance?

95
00:10:56.190 --> 00:10:58.000
Chief!

96
00:10:58.000 --> 00:11:06.100
Geez. I was planning to get some sleep
because I have to work later!

97
00:11:08.290 --> 00:11:10.400
Such is Anna's plight.

98
00:11:10.900 --> 00:11:14.690
It's better to leave her to die than to
expose her existence to the world.

99
00:11:15.790 --> 00:11:17.600
Do you get it now?

100
00:11:17.600 --> 00:11:20.100
And what better opportunity
would we have had than today

101
00:11:20.100 --> 00:11:25.290
when you gave her strawberries and she
willingly ate them. knowing she'd die?

102
00:11:25.290 --> 00:11:29.100
Even Assemblyman Jang couldn't
say anything about this.

103
00:11:29.100 --> 00:11:33.000
Who's the person who
sent back the ambulance?

104
00:11:38.600 --> 00:11:40.900
What are you going to do about it
regardless of who it may have been?

105
00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:43.400
No matter what you do.
Anna's circumstances won't change.

106
00:11:43.900 --> 00:11:48.290
The only thing you can do is
to protect her at all costs!

107
00:11:48.790 --> 00:11:52.790
If you'd taken Anna
to a hospital before

108
00:11:52.790 --> 00:11:54.940
we all would've been done for.

109
00:11:54.940 --> 00:11:58.900
Mi Ran. the housekeeper.
and the doctors at the ER too!

110
00:11:59.900 --> 00:12:02.100
In other words.
everyone who knows about Anna.

111
00:12:04.790 --> 00:12:09.100
Well. you would've been an exception
since you're a member of Cloud Nine.

112
00:12:10.900 --> 00:12:14.970
Did you already forget why the old
people at the orchard almost died?

113
00:12:14.970 --> 00:12:18.100
Acting this way
is quite unlike you.

114
00:12:18.100 --> 00:12:22.190
If they know you're acting this way.
it'll be harder for you to protect Anna!

115
00:12:22.690 --> 00:12:26.000
If you really want to protect her.
act as you always do.

116
00:12:29.100 --> 00:12:30.690
Go on now.

117
00:12:34.190 --> 00:12:35.790
Damn it.

118
00:12:43.190 --> 00:12:48.000
Make sure you watch over
that poor child well. all right?

119
00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:50.000
Do you know Anna?

120
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:52.190
Not well. no.

121
00:12:52.190 --> 00:12:59.690
I only know that she's been forced
to go abroad due to having bad parents.

122
00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:03.400
Yes. you could say that again.
She has terrible parents.

123
00:13:03.900 --> 00:13:09.000
Damn it. And her dad is the
presidential candidate. of all things.

124
00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:10.190
Damn it.

125
00:13:10.690 --> 00:13:12.400
Who's her father?

126
00:13:12.400 --> 00:13:16.190
That girl's last name is Go.
Her name is Go Anna.

127
00:13:16.190 --> 00:13:19.500
She's not legally
Jang Se Joon's daughter.

128
00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:21.400
Her last name is "Go"?

129
00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:23.600
You didn't know?
Her last name definitely is "Go."

130
00:13:23.600 --> 00:13:28.690
There was a referee by the name
of Go Am Wook. An American.

131
00:13:28.690 --> 00:13:33.000
Her mother. Um Hye Rin.
got married to that guy!

132
00:13:33.500 --> 00:13:37.600
Wait. Then Jang Se Joon
seduced a married woman and...

133
00:13:37.600 --> 00:13:39.900
No. that's not it!

134
00:13:39.900 --> 00:13:41.100
Well. it's complicated.

135
00:13:41.100 --> 00:13:45.190
That's... wow. I've lived
quite long. haven't I?

136
00:13:45.190 --> 00:13:47.690
So what happened is

137
00:13:47.690 --> 00:13:53.600
she did get married to the American.
but she was already pregnant by then!

138
00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:56.190
With Jang Se Joon's child!

139
00:13:56.690 --> 00:13:58.690
You get what I'm saying now?

140
00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:04.290
I didn't know that she was
pregnant back then either!

141
00:14:04.290 --> 00:14:09.500
But I don't know what happened.
Maybe she was abused by her husband.

142
00:14:09.500 --> 00:14:12.400
But Um Hye Rin. who'd gone to America.
appeared with Anna in her arms

143
00:14:12.400 --> 00:14:20.190
in front of Jang Se Joon. who was
happily married to Choi Yoo Jin!

144
00:14:20.190 --> 00:14:21.900
You understand what
I'm saying. right?

145
00:14:21.900 --> 00:14:31.100
He acted like a family with them
behind Choi Yoo Jin's back.

146
00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:35.790
But that young girl had
such a terrible fate.

147
00:14:35.790 --> 00:14:39.190
Her mother ended
having a violent death!

148
00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:41.690
And she was dragged abroad
shortly after that.

149
00:14:41.690 --> 00:14:44.400
That's why I'm saying that
she's a pitiful child.

150
00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:46.600
A violent... death?

151
00:14:46.600 --> 00:14:50.000
Oh. you mean Um Hye Rin?

152
00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.400
Well. yeah.
Suicides are gruesome things. after all.

153
00:14:53.400 --> 00:14:54.600
Isn't that right?

154
00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:59.290
Oh yeah. I don't know if Choi Yoo
Jin will continue to let her live

155
00:14:59.290 --> 00:15:03.600
if she keeps acting up like this.

156
00:15:11.790 --> 00:15:14.000
So. did you give
it some thought?

157
00:15:14.000 --> 00:15:16.100
Why are you in such a rush?

158
00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:17.900
Let's eat first.

159
00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:21.190
The acorn jelly here
is quite good.

160
00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:24.400
I'm sure that you don't have much time.

161
00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:28.190
Since it's been a while
since "that" has started.

162
00:15:29.690 --> 00:15:35.900
It seems that the president still can't
forgive you and Assemblyman Jang.

163
00:15:35.900 --> 00:15:39.400
He doesn't want you two
to betray him. the former president

164
00:15:39.400 --> 00:15:44.000
after he helps you
two into the Blue House...

165
00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:46.690
Are you sure that you're not just
eyeing the position for yourself?

166
00:16:00.100 --> 00:16:01.100
<i>[REPORTS OF GOINGS-ON
AROUND PRESIDENT - 2016]</i>

167
00:16:01.100 --> 00:16:04.690
These are the things I've noticed
happening around the president.

168
00:16:04.690 --> 00:16:08.000
Of course. this doesn't include
everything that's already happened.

169
00:16:08.500 --> 00:16:10.400
Is this... a threat?

170
00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:19.000
<i>[INSIDE INFORMATION REGARDING PYEONGCHANG
SCHOLARSHIP FOUNDATION - TOP SECRET]</i>

171
00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:24.690
These are secret documents regarding
the Foundation and JB Group.

172
00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:27.500
All in.

173
00:16:32.100 --> 00:16:34.690
You could squash me so easily
with the information in there.

174
00:16:34.690 --> 00:16:39.690
So you're proposing that
we share our weaknesses?

175
00:16:40.500 --> 00:16:41.600
Yes.

176
00:16:43.100 --> 00:16:47.600
Is that enough for you
to make a deal with me?

177
00:16:54.600 --> 00:16:56.690
As to be expected of you.

178
00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:01.000
I'm sorry.
We're closed for the day.

179
00:17:01.000 --> 00:17:03.400
Hey. come on.
There are still people in there!

180
00:17:03.400 --> 00:17:04.400
The lights are on too!

181
00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:06.690
They're our last
customers of the day.

182
00:17:06.690 --> 00:17:09.400
Come on. Let me just get
a sip of makgeoli and go.

183
00:17:10.630 --> 00:17:12.500
Must you force yourself in?

184
00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:16.600
Looks like this place
does some great business.

185
00:17:16.600 --> 00:17:18.190
They even pick and choose
their customers too.

186
00:17:18.190 --> 00:17:19.290
Let's go.

187
00:17:29.190 --> 00:17:30.690
Yes. it's me.

188
00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:39.400
I understand why Chairman Choi.
your younger brother. fears you now.

189
00:17:39.400 --> 00:17:40.600
That's a compliment. right?

190
00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:41.990
Oh. of course!

191
00:17:41.990 --> 00:17:46.400
How could I dare insult the one who will
be the First-in-Command in this country?

192
00:17:46.900 --> 00:17:48.690
It's a compliment.

193
00:17:48.690 --> 00:17:50.900
That's not quite right.

194
00:17:50.900 --> 00:17:54.190
My husband will be the one
who'll be First-in-Command.

195
00:17:54.400 --> 00:17:55.400
Excuse me?

196
00:17:55.990 --> 00:17:57.800
Oh. is that right?

197
00:17:57.800 --> 00:17:58.990
What?

198
00:18:03.190 --> 00:18:08.800
All right. then. When would
you like to join our party?

199
00:18:08.800 --> 00:18:13.190
We can't just quietly slink in. right?

200
00:18:13.690 --> 00:18:22.800
I'm preparing a nice show. but I'd like
for you to clear the way for us first.

201
00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:30.900
Really? All right.

202
00:19:00.400 --> 00:19:02.500
Did the meeting go...

203
00:19:05.100 --> 00:19:06.800
It went well. didn't it?

204
00:19:06.800 --> 00:19:08.100
Does it seem that way?

205
00:19:08.100 --> 00:19:10.190
Congratulations. Madam.

206
00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:11.600
Thank you.

207
00:19:17.190 --> 00:19:19.690
What a beautiful night!

208
00:19:27.100 --> 00:19:28.400
You don't believe me?

209
00:19:28.400 --> 00:19:29.400
What?

210
00:19:45.990 --> 00:19:49.400
Will they be able
to enter the party then?

211
00:19:49.900 --> 00:19:51.490
Probably.

212
00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:54.990
Because every country has
corrupt people behind the scenes

213
00:19:54.990 --> 00:19:58.690
and dirty businesspeople
within their government.

214
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:02.800
I never would've guessed.

215
00:20:03.300 --> 00:20:09.190
So he ended up collaborating with
Choi Yoo Jin in the end. after all.

216
00:20:09.690 --> 00:20:12.490
Then take care of our
internal organization

217
00:20:12.490 --> 00:20:14.800
and prepare a vote
within our party.

218
00:20:16.900 --> 00:20:19.100
Will you be able to do that?

219
00:20:19.100 --> 00:20:20.100
Sir?

220
00:20:21.600 --> 00:20:27.400
The one who exposes and banishes what
is dirty and rotten will become the hero.

221
00:20:33.100 --> 00:20:36.690
Where did you say
Jang Se Joon is now. again?

222
00:20:44.490 --> 00:20:48.600
Assemblyman.
Madam's meeting has just ended.

223
00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:52.690
Oh. And judging from your expression.
I assume that it went well?

224
00:20:53.190 --> 00:20:54.600
Yes. sir.

225
00:20:54.600 --> 00:20:55.900
Really?

226
00:20:55.900 --> 00:21:00.190
Then we'll have to change some of
the content for today too. won't we?

227
00:21:00.190 --> 00:21:02.100
We can't cross the people
at the Blue House.

228
00:21:02.100 --> 00:21:05.400
That's right. You'll have to
come on a bit softer today.

229
00:21:05.400 --> 00:21:06.990
I'll get the questions changed too.

230
00:21:07.490 --> 00:21:10.190
All right.
Go on. now.

231
00:21:10.190 --> 00:21:11.190
Yes. sir.

232
00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:38.690
Congratulations. Madam.

233
00:21:38.690 --> 00:21:39.990
No need for that.

234
00:21:39.990 --> 00:21:42.100
How's that child doing?

235
00:21:42.100 --> 00:21:43.690
She's in the infirmary. Madam.

236
00:21:43.690 --> 00:21:46.900
Really? So she survived the trip here.

237
00:21:46.900 --> 00:21:48.100
I apologize.

238
00:21:48.100 --> 00:21:52.100
Why are you sorry?
That's just her fate.

239
00:21:54.600 --> 00:21:56.400
Where's the infirmary?

240
00:21:56.400 --> 00:21:58.400
What? You want to see her. ma'am?

241
00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:02.100
Yeah. You go on ahead
to Cloud Nine. Chief Kim.

242
00:22:02.190 --> 00:22:05.190
- Where is it?
- Oh. I'll guide you there.

243
00:22:20.900 --> 00:22:23.100
How's her condition?
Can she manage a conversation?

244
00:22:23.100 --> 00:22:26.100
Yes. Her body is
a lot better now

245
00:22:26.100 --> 00:22:29.690
but we'll have to get her psychological
help due to her suicide attempt...

246
00:22:29.690 --> 00:22:30.690
A hospital?

247
00:22:30.690 --> 00:22:32.490
No need.

248
00:22:33.690 --> 00:22:36.900
Just do a better job watching over her
so that she doesn't do anything stupid.

249
00:22:52.990 --> 00:22:55.100
Leave for a bit.
All of you.

250
00:22:55.600 --> 00:22:56.600
Oh. yes. Madam.

251
00:23:01.490 --> 00:23:04.100
Hey! Follow me!

252
00:23:04.100 --> 00:23:06.190
A hospital? Seriously?

253
00:23:17.100 --> 00:23:18.300
What?

254
00:23:32.490 --> 00:23:35.990
That nun outfit looked
quite good on you.

255
00:23:35.990 --> 00:23:37.900
And your singing voice
was quite touching too.

256
00:23:40.900 --> 00:23:43.100
Did you learn that at the nunnery?

257
00:23:45.800 --> 00:23:47.690
But. you know...

258
00:23:48.190 --> 00:23:51.600
just what were you expecting
when you showed up there?

259
00:23:52.190 --> 00:23:57.300
Did you think that I was interfering
so that your father couldn't see you?

260
00:23:59.690 --> 00:24:02.690
You saw him at the church
today too. right?

261
00:24:06.100 --> 00:24:07.400
<i>Dad.</i>

262
00:24:19.300 --> 00:24:21.700
Why... is Anna...

263
00:24:26.800 --> 00:24:31.690
Your dad doesn't want
to meet with you.

264
00:24:33.100 --> 00:24:36.300
Your dad won't show up here.

265
00:24:36.300 --> 00:24:41.600
Just like how he didn't show up
when your mom Um Hye Rin died

266
00:24:41.600 --> 00:24:44.100
or when you left for Spain.

267
00:24:46.100 --> 00:24:49.600
I'm sure it hurts.
Yeah.

268
00:24:51.100 --> 00:24:54.400
And I'm sure you want to
deny this because of that.

269
00:24:55.100 --> 00:24:57.300
But this is reality.

270
00:24:57.990 --> 00:24:59.990
Dads are all like that.

271
00:24:59.990 --> 00:25:04.600
I know this
since I'm someone's daughter too

272
00:25:04.600 --> 00:25:11.190
but daughters all have special
feelings toward their dads.

273
00:25:11.900 --> 00:25:16.800
But... dads are all kind of like that.

274
00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:21.600
They don't know how we feel.

275
00:25:22.100 --> 00:25:28.800
<i>I'm sure you thought that
you were all your dad had left</i>

276
00:25:28.800 --> 00:25:31.190
but you don't mean
that much to him.

277
00:25:31.190 --> 00:25:36.900
You're a small. burdensome
fragment from his past.

278
00:25:43.400 --> 00:25:45.800
Then let me meet Dad.

279
00:25:46.400 --> 00:25:49.100
- I'll ask him myself...
- How?

280
00:25:49.600 --> 00:25:52.190
You want me to drag him here
against his will?

281
00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:57.400
Even a couple in love needs to mind their
manners toward each other. you know.

282
00:25:57.400 --> 00:26:01.300
You dad doesn't want to see you.
so what do you want me to do?

283
00:26:04.300 --> 00:26:09.690
Dad... doesn't love you.

284
00:26:20.400 --> 00:26:25.190
Is that what your mother told you?

285
00:26:27.100 --> 00:26:30.900
Sure. I understand how
she must have felt.

286
00:26:31.400 --> 00:26:33.990
She must've hated me
quite a bit.

287
00:26:34.490 --> 00:26:36.600
But. Anna.

288
00:26:37.600 --> 00:26:42.190
There's something you didn't know about
your mom. since you were too young.

289
00:26:42.690 --> 00:26:45.100
<i>It's hard for people like us
to understand.</i>

290
00:26:45.720 --> 00:26:49.690
<i>But do you know what the life goal
for all assemblymen is?</i>

291
00:26:50.400 --> 00:26:52.990
It's to be re-elected
during the next election cycle.

292
00:26:52.990 --> 00:26:55.690
Your dad's no exception.

293
00:26:55.690 --> 00:26:58.190
However. do you know
what your mom said to him then?

294
00:26:58.690 --> 00:27:04.190
Your mom was using you
to blackmail your dad.

295
00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:06.300
With the election coming up. too.

296
00:27:08.490 --> 00:27:13.400
She may have been
a good mother to you. but...

297
00:27:14.690 --> 00:27:15.900
well. figures.

298
00:27:15.900 --> 00:27:19.490
I'm sure it was hard for you as well.
since your mother was an alcoholic.

299
00:27:19.990 --> 00:27:24.190
How else could you have given her
those pills with your own hands?

300
00:27:24.690 --> 00:27:26.750
That's not true.

301
00:27:26.750 --> 00:27:29.690
My mom didn't die because
of the sleeping pills I brought her.

302
00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:32.920
There was someone at my house then.

303
00:27:32.920 --> 00:27:34.800
And they tried to kill me too.

304
00:27:36.190 --> 00:27:37.600
So?

305
00:27:39.100 --> 00:27:40.800
Was that me?

306
00:27:41.990 --> 00:27:48.600
Anna. Your memories
are lying to you.

307
00:27:48.600 --> 00:27:52.800
Sometimes. the truth is
just too unbelievable.

308
00:27:53.400 --> 00:27:56.900
But... this is the truth.

309
00:27:56.900 --> 00:28:02.400
Your mom died because
of the pills you gave her.

310
00:28:02.400 --> 00:28:05.330
Lies. I heard everything
from our old housekeeper.

311
00:28:05.330 --> 00:28:06.690
Your old housekeeper?

312
00:28:06.690 --> 00:28:12.190
<i>Oh. the lady who you went to see
before at the assisted living facility?</i>

313
00:28:12.800 --> 00:28:14.100
Anna.

314
00:28:14.100 --> 00:28:20.690
If I did kill your mother and that
woman had known about that...

315
00:28:21.190 --> 00:28:24.190
do you really think that
I would've let that woman live?

316
00:28:34.900 --> 00:28:36.800
Please. stop it already.

317
00:28:44.490 --> 00:28:46.300
Anna is quite ill.

318
00:28:51.190 --> 00:28:52.600
Figures.

319
00:28:53.900 --> 00:28:56.900
Looks like I've said way too many
unnecessary things today.

320
00:28:56.900 --> 00:28:59.100
And to an ill person too.

321
00:28:59.100 --> 00:29:00.690
All right. Anna.

322
00:29:01.190 --> 00:29:05.800
You must be tired too. since you've been
on the run since early this morning.

323
00:29:06.300 --> 00:29:08.100
Get some rest.

324
00:29:09.300 --> 00:29:11.190
And take good care of yourself.

325
00:29:26.900 --> 00:29:28.800
Come to Cloud Nine.

326
00:29:45.340 --> 00:29:46.490
Don't cry.

327
00:29:47.600 --> 00:29:48.990
And wait.

328
00:29:50.400 --> 00:29:52.490
I'll bring your dad to you.

329
00:30:52.300 --> 00:30:54.100
What brings you here?

330
00:30:55.800 --> 00:30:57.800
I wanted to see
Assemblyman Jang's appearance.

331
00:30:57.800 --> 00:30:59.990
What?
See his appearance?

332
00:31:00.990 --> 00:31:02.490
What the hell are you planning now?

333
00:31:02.490 --> 00:31:04.400
Nothing!

334
00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:05.800
But that person...

335
00:31:07.190 --> 00:31:08.490
Who?

336
00:31:10.400 --> 00:31:11.900
It's nothing.

337
00:31:11.900 --> 00:31:12.900
Hey!

338
00:31:13.750 --> 00:31:16.100
What a rude punk.

339
00:31:17.190 --> 00:31:22.100
All right. everyone.
It's been tough lately. hasn't it?

340
00:31:22.100 --> 00:31:23.690
- Yes!
- Yes!

341
00:31:24.190 --> 00:31:28.690
Yes. that's right. We're standing
at a crossroads right now.

342
00:31:28.690 --> 00:31:33.900
The poor are getting poorer
while the rich are getting richer.

343
00:31:33.900 --> 00:31:35.900
The number of elderly people
we have is increasing

344
00:31:35.900 --> 00:31:40.400
but the number of young people paying
into pension funds is decreasing.

345
00:31:40.400 --> 00:31:46.100
However. the younger generation is
crying out. saying there are no jobs.

346
00:31:46.100 --> 00:31:48.100
The rich and poor
are at odds with one another

347
00:31:48.100 --> 00:31:50.600
and the old and the young harbor
hostility toward one another.

348
00:31:50.600 --> 00:31:54.600
What's worse. those who love
each other and want to marry...

349
00:31:54.600 --> 00:31:55.900
This is K2.

350
00:31:55.900 --> 00:31:59.490
There's a suspicious character near
the front of the stage. at the middle.

351
00:31:59.490 --> 00:32:03.400
Our population is aging fast. but the
marriage and birth rates are quite low!

352
00:32:03.400 --> 00:32:05.690
This is Team Leader Seo.
What do you mean by that?

353
00:32:06.190 --> 00:32:07.990
Why is that?

354
00:32:07.990 --> 00:32:10.400
"It's the economy. stupid!"

355
00:32:10.400 --> 00:32:14.690
It's the economy. stupid!

356
00:32:15.190 --> 00:32:19.900
Well. of course. I'm not
calling you all idiots.

357
00:32:21.100 --> 00:32:25.300
10 o'clock. 11 o'clock. 12 o'clock.
and 2 o'clock from the upstage center.

358
00:32:25.300 --> 00:32:27.300
<i>They have something
suspicious on them.</i>

359
00:32:27.300 --> 00:32:33.300
The guys sitting at B12 and C16
are hiding something.

360
00:32:33.300 --> 00:32:35.400
The issue still remains
with the economy.

361
00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:39.400
Team Leader here. Those people
passed the security check before.

362
00:32:39.400 --> 00:32:40.990
They're fine.

363
00:32:42.800 --> 00:32:48.800
Oh. but someone told me that if
I feel pain. I should go to the hospital.

364
00:32:49.300 --> 00:32:50.800
That's right!

365
00:32:50.800 --> 00:32:53.900
Looks like there's another
person in pain right there.

366
00:32:57.190 --> 00:32:58.600
Yes. that's right.

367
00:32:58.600 --> 00:33:01.800
We're all in pain right now.

368
00:33:25.900 --> 00:33:30.690
I'm sorry to ask this of your generation
when you're busy looking for jobs

369
00:33:30.690 --> 00:33:33.900
but to be honest. my generation
didn't study too hard.

370
00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:35.800
We were busy with dates. firstly.

371
00:33:35.800 --> 00:33:40.990
But a guy like me. who's ugly.
didn't get asked out a lot.

372
00:33:41.490 --> 00:33:46.100
I was able to pass the bar exam in
my junior year. And with top scores.

373
00:33:50.690 --> 00:33:53.990
Yes. I am bragging.

374
00:33:55.300 --> 00:33:57.100
I'm sorry.

375
00:34:00.190 --> 00:34:05.190
Secondly. we didn't have to study if
we were involved in political protests.

376
00:34:05.190 --> 00:34:09.800
Who'd care about grades. after all.
when the country is in turmoil?

377
00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:14.600
So we didn't worry about getting
married or getting a job.

378
00:34:14.600 --> 00:34:18.300
Why? Because the country
was in turmoil!

379
00:34:19.800 --> 00:34:24.190
To be honest. it was because our
standard of living was getting better.

380
00:34:24.690 --> 00:34:26.600
There were tons of jobs to be had!

381
00:34:26.600 --> 00:34:30.800
And we didn't worry
even if prices of things were rising!

382
00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:32.300
K2 here.

383
00:34:32.300 --> 00:34:35.800
Stop the show.
The VIP is in danger.

384
00:34:35.800 --> 00:34:36.800
Now.

385
00:34:36.800 --> 00:34:39.380
Are you crazy?
K2. Where are you?

386
00:34:39.390 --> 00:34:41.090
Backstage.

387
00:34:41.890 --> 00:34:51.090
This is why the elderly say now that
things were much better back in the day.

388
00:34:52.020 --> 00:34:54.300
However. how are things now?

389
00:34:56.030 --> 00:34:59.150
"It's the economy. stupid!"

390
00:34:59.150 --> 00:35:02.300
It's the economy. stupid!

391
00:35:10.390 --> 00:35:13.090
Stop doing useless things
and just sit still.

392
00:35:14.300 --> 00:35:17.890
I went on a date with my wife.

393
00:35:18.390 --> 00:35:24.900
I was a poor guy without
a single cent in my pocket...

394
00:35:32.240 --> 00:35:36.190
Hey. K1!
What are you doing here?

395
00:35:36.190 --> 00:35:38.400
Move before you damage
the goods. got it?

396
00:35:40.090 --> 00:35:42.590
You must be destroyed!

397
00:35:48.090 --> 00:35:51.490
Jang Se Joon. who hates international
finance! Wake up from your delusions!

398
00:35:51.490 --> 00:35:52.990
- Wake up! Wake up!
- Wake up! Wake up!

399
00:36:03.890 --> 00:36:05.300
Wait!

400
00:36:07.090 --> 00:36:11.250
Let go of those people.

401
00:36:11.250 --> 00:36:14.200
Do not cover those people's mouths!

402
00:36:14.700 --> 00:36:18.590
These people don't deserve
to be treated this way.

403
00:36:18.590 --> 00:36:24.800
These people have the right to throw eggs
at me and the other Korean politicians!

404
00:36:25.300 --> 00:36:31.590
And that's because these people have been
let down by so many politicians thus far.

405
00:36:38.700 --> 00:36:43.800
And I'm not going to die just because
I'm pelted by a couple of eggs.

406
00:36:47.090 --> 00:36:52.470
And if these people really
wanted to hurt me

407
00:36:52.470 --> 00:36:53.800
they would've thrown stones. not eggs.

408
00:36:53.800 --> 00:36:55.590
Isn't that right?

409
00:36:55.590 --> 00:36:57.490
- Yes.
- Yes.

410
00:36:58.090 --> 00:37:02.300
It's because these people
have affection toward me

411
00:37:02.300 --> 00:37:05.300
that they threw eggs at me.
That's what I believe.

412
00:37:05.300 --> 00:37:09.800
And the thing they chanted.
"Wake up." Isn't that right?

413
00:37:09.800 --> 00:37:13.590
If I am a politician.
I do need to wake up.

414
00:37:13.590 --> 00:37:17.590
I understand.
I'll do that.

415
00:37:27.090 --> 00:37:29.800
I will wake up.

416
00:37:41.700 --> 00:37:48.300
I demand the prosecution
start a strict investigation right away

417
00:37:48.300 --> 00:37:53.890
on the International Finance Group.
who these people believe that I hate

418
00:37:53.890 --> 00:37:58.990
which has been far too
suspicious as of late.

419
00:38:00.390 --> 00:38:04.590
Furthermore. as of now

420
00:38:04.590 --> 00:38:10.390
I will not exercise the immunity
given to me as an assemblyman

421
00:38:10.390 --> 00:38:17.090
and will head to the prosecutor's office
tomorrow morning to be investigated.

422
00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:24.890
Furthermore. I will submit to
a search and seizure

423
00:38:24.890 --> 00:38:30.300
at all locations related to me. including
my home. office. and election office

424
00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:38.200
and ask that they will find and expose
any hint of corruption. if there is any.

425
00:38:38.990 --> 00:38:46.300
And if the search yields anything that
sparks the slightest hint of suspicion

426
00:38:46.300 --> 00:38:53.200
I will pull out of the presidential
race as your candidate.

427
00:39:03.890 --> 00:39:07.890
To those of you who
threw eggs at me today.

428
00:39:07.890 --> 00:39:16.800
If you're satisfied with the results
that this investigation yields

429
00:39:16.800 --> 00:39:25.090
please don't waste eggs by throwing them
and just give them to me instead.

430
00:39:26.390 --> 00:39:28.990
It's fine to attack me with
eggs and all that

431
00:39:30.490 --> 00:39:34.300
but I'd rather bring them to
my wife. who loves to cook. and...

432
00:39:40.800 --> 00:39:42.990
be loved by her even more.

433
00:39:48.200 --> 00:40:08.990
- Jang Se Hoon!
- Jang Se Hoon!

434
00:40:10.520 --> 00:40:13.890
Man. this reeks.

435
00:40:13.890 --> 00:40:16.700
I reek. don't I?

436
00:40:16.700 --> 00:40:17.700
It's all right.

437
00:40:17.700 --> 00:40:19.490
Those punks.
I told them to only throw two or so.

438
00:40:19.490 --> 00:40:21.300
Why'd they throw so many?

439
00:40:21.890 --> 00:40:24.590
Is there some pent-up frustration
toward me or something?

440
00:40:24.590 --> 00:40:27.300
But still. this stunt had
a great effect.

441
00:40:27.300 --> 00:40:28.590
You have some pent-up
frustration toward me too. don't you?

442
00:40:28.590 --> 00:40:32.090
What? Of course not.
Maybe love. but not frustration.

443
00:40:35.090 --> 00:40:40.590
I need to shower. so that's
going to take a bit of time.

444
00:40:41.700 --> 00:40:43.300
I'll call you when I'm done.

445
00:40:43.300 --> 00:40:44.490
Yes. sir.

446
00:40:47.390 --> 00:40:48.590
Oh geez.

447
00:40:51.800 --> 00:40:53.490
I kept you waiting. didn't I?

448
00:40:54.590 --> 00:40:56.300
Geez.

449
00:41:01.590 --> 00:41:02.990
Have you eaten?

450
00:41:02.990 --> 00:41:04.590
- Yes.
- Oh.

451
00:41:06.090 --> 00:41:10.300
I'm going to head in first.
so come in quickly. Okay?

452
00:41:10.800 --> 00:41:12.300
Yes. sir.

453
00:41:12.990 --> 00:41:17.090
Oh. what a cutie.

454
00:41:23.300 --> 00:41:25.590
Why don't we get some coffee?

455
00:41:25.590 --> 00:41:27.700
Who knows how long this
will take. after all?

456
00:41:30.590 --> 00:41:32.590
You stand by here. okay?

457
00:41:32.590 --> 00:41:33.890
Yes. sir.

458
00:41:39.700 --> 00:41:42.290
What are you doing?
Come in!

459
00:41:42.290 --> 00:41:44.200
Yes. I'm coming.

460
00:42:24.220 --> 00:42:36.220
Subtitles by DramaFever
Synced by NChoerunnisa

461
00:42:37.890 --> 00:42:39.490
Here you are.

462
00:42:40.790 --> 00:42:43.090
Get your clothes on.
You need to get out of here.

463
00:42:55.090 --> 00:42:57.590
- Who are you?
- Police! Move!

464
00:42:57.590 --> 00:43:02.200
- Stop right there!
- Stop!

465
00:43:04.490 --> 00:43:06.400
- Who's this?
- He's on the same side as that woman.

466
00:43:06.400 --> 00:43:07.490
What?

467
00:43:07.490 --> 00:43:10.390
And the cops will be forcing
their way in here any minute now.

468
00:43:10.430 --> 00:43:11.990
Since the cops are on their side too.

469
00:43:21.090 --> 00:43:22.990
Do you want to be arrested. damn it?

470
00:43:28.240 --> 00:43:29.300
Don't look at them.

471
00:43:29.300 --> 00:43:30.300
There he is!
Get him!

472
00:43:30.300 --> 00:43:31.300
Run!

473
00:43:35.490 --> 00:43:36.700
Stop!

474
00:43:36.700 --> 00:43:38.300
Stop right there!

475
00:43:38.300 --> 00:43:39.390
Move!

476
00:43:41.300 --> 00:43:42.800
What's going on?

477
00:43:42.800 --> 00:43:44.990
The cops set a trap.
I'll leave it to you. Thanks!

478
00:43:48.990 --> 00:43:51.490
- What's with those guys?
- They're Park Kwan Soo's cronies.

479
00:43:51.490 --> 00:43:52.990
A trap?

480
00:43:56.090 --> 00:43:58.090
Geez. you bastards.

481
00:43:58.090 --> 00:44:01.300
You do know that this is
an obstruction of justice. right?

482
00:44:01.300 --> 00:44:03.200
Go ahead and arrest me. then.

483
00:44:05.140 --> 00:44:06.990
The suspect has fled the scene.
Block the entrance.

484
00:44:06.990 --> 00:44:09.990
Hey. secure the CCTV footage.

485
00:44:09.990 --> 00:44:12.300
And show me your arrest warrant.

486
00:44:12.300 --> 00:44:14.700
Though you probably don't have one since
you planned this and waited outside.

487
00:44:14.700 --> 00:44:17.890
A warrant?
I don't need that.

488
00:44:17.890 --> 00:44:20.200
The victim called us
and reported him for sexual assault.

489
00:44:20.200 --> 00:44:23.090
Chief Joo! Look.

490
00:44:23.090 --> 00:44:24.890
These two were on the same side.

491
00:44:27.890 --> 00:44:31.990
Call the Central Office and report that
the cops conspired to kill a politician.

492
00:44:31.990 --> 00:44:33.300
And send out the photo evidence too!

493
00:44:33.300 --> 00:44:34.490
Yes. sir.

494
00:44:45.090 --> 00:44:46.300
<i>We lost them!</i>

495
00:44:48.280 --> 00:44:52.300
All right. I think the show is over now.

496
00:44:57.890 --> 00:45:01.090
Yeah.
See you next time. then.

497
00:45:10.090 --> 00:45:13.990
Oh man. that was a close one!

498
00:45:17.610 --> 00:45:20.090
Wow. thanks.

499
00:45:20.090 --> 00:45:21.090
No problem. sir.

500
00:45:21.090 --> 00:45:25.490
No. really. If it hadn't been for you.
I would've been in big trouble.

501
00:45:25.490 --> 00:45:27.300
Yes. I'm sure.

502
00:45:29.990 --> 00:45:32.590
But. um. where are we headed?

503
00:45:32.590 --> 00:45:34.490
To meet with your daughter.

504
00:45:34.490 --> 00:45:35.490
What?

505
00:45:37.780 --> 00:45:39.200
Stop the car.

506
00:45:44.710 --> 00:45:45.800
Stop the car. damn it!

507
00:45:45.800 --> 00:45:47.400
If you don't want to
freaking see her...

508
00:45:48.200 --> 00:45:51.200
If you don't want to see her.
go and tell her that to her face.

509
00:45:51.700 --> 00:45:54.090
Instead of giving
a young woman false hopes.

510
00:45:56.990 --> 00:45:59.990
Who ordered you
to do something like this?

511
00:45:59.990 --> 00:46:01.890
I'm not the type to do something
like this because I'm told to.

512
00:46:01.890 --> 00:46:03.990
This bastard!

513
00:46:06.340 --> 00:46:09.590
Do you think you'll be okay
after doing something like this?

514
00:46:09.590 --> 00:46:10.800
You know. dogs...

515
00:46:12.650 --> 00:46:16.300
even have a sense of duty to protect
puppies that they've taken in.

516
00:46:16.300 --> 00:46:17.390
And here. you have a child.

517
00:46:17.390 --> 00:46:19.610
Shouldn't you supervise her. at the very
least. if she's such an inconvenience?

518
00:46:19.610 --> 00:46:21.500
You impudent little punk!
How dare you...

519
00:46:21.500 --> 00:46:23.720
Do you...

520
00:46:23.720 --> 00:46:25.890
know where I found Anna today?

521
00:46:28.110 --> 00:46:29.590
Dream Land.

522
00:46:34.470 --> 00:46:35.990
Do you remember now?

523
00:46:37.700 --> 00:46:42.590
Do you know
what she said when I found her?

524
00:46:43.700 --> 00:46:48.010
He's not mad that I suddenly
appeared out of nowhere?

525
00:46:48.010 --> 00:46:49.700
She was worrying about you.

526
00:46:52.990 --> 00:46:54.700
But now I know the truth.

527
00:46:56.430 --> 00:47:00.090
That the bad person who'd been
bothering my dad so much

528
00:47:00.090 --> 00:47:02.090
was me all along.

529
00:47:07.300 --> 00:47:10.090
What?
She ate strawberries?

530
00:47:13.200 --> 00:47:15.210
She has a severe allergy.
so if she eats them...

531
00:47:15.210 --> 00:47:16.600
Yes. that's right!

532
00:47:16.600 --> 00:47:18.010
That's right.

533
00:47:18.010 --> 00:47:20.590
She... she could die.

534
00:47:23.520 --> 00:47:24.520
Anna...

535
00:47:26.500 --> 00:47:29.200
didn't try to commit suicide
because she hates you. I think.

536
00:47:29.990 --> 00:47:33.800
It's because she realized that she's
a burdensome existence in your life...

537
00:47:36.720 --> 00:47:39.490
and tried to disappear quietly.
That's probably why she ate it.

538
00:48:09.970 --> 00:48:15.280
If you really did all this
just for Anna's sake

539
00:48:15.280 --> 00:48:16.490
promise me this.

540
00:48:18.010 --> 00:48:21.590
That you'll protect her
until the very end.

541
00:48:22.090 --> 00:48:23.800
If you do. I'll meet with her.

542
00:48:27.300 --> 00:48:28.700
Sure.

543
00:48:30.820 --> 00:48:32.300
I promise.

544
00:48:40.070 --> 00:48:41.140
Yes. Chief?

545
00:48:41.140 --> 00:48:42.790
<i>Hey! Why haven't you
been picking up?</i>

546
00:48:43.600 --> 00:48:44.890
<i>Where are you right now?</i>

547
00:48:47.390 --> 00:48:49.100
<i>I asked you where you are. punk!</i>

548
00:48:49.100 --> 00:48:51.000
It's me. Chief Joo.

549
00:48:51.000 --> 00:48:53.890
Geez. You're going to blow out
my eardrums at this rate.

550
00:48:55.130 --> 00:48:56.130
I apologize. Assemblyman.

551
00:48:56.130 --> 00:48:58.990
I'm at JSS Headquarters right now.

552
00:48:58.990 --> 00:49:00.290
<i>Come here to pick me up.</i>

553
00:49:00.290 --> 00:49:01.890
Yes. sir.

554
00:49:07.910 --> 00:49:11.100
The reason why I didn't meet
Anna for all this time

555
00:49:11.100 --> 00:49:14.890
is because me seeing her
puts her in danger.

556
00:49:14.890 --> 00:49:19.990
I've sold my soul to the devil
for the sake of my own greed.

557
00:49:19.990 --> 00:49:25.390
And due to that. I've lost
my morals and the people I love.

558
00:49:25.990 --> 00:49:32.990
But this thing called greed
doesn't come with brakes.

559
00:49:32.990 --> 00:49:39.290
I need to speed up even more in order
to escape Choi Yoo Jin's clutches.

560
00:49:42.920 --> 00:49:44.790
Anna is a hostage.

561
00:49:46.540 --> 00:49:50.100
I can only save her if I gain
the ultimate amount of power.

562
00:49:50.600 --> 00:49:57.490
If I turn back now. Choi Yoo Jin will
deem Anna useless as a hostage.

563
00:49:57.990 --> 00:50:01.290
And if that happens.
Anna will be in danger.

564
00:50:02.350 --> 00:50:07.080
If I meet with Anna
and say even one wrong thing

565
00:50:07.080 --> 00:50:11.360
Choi Yoo Jin will realize
what I'm trying to do

566
00:50:11.360 --> 00:50:15.100
and hide Anna where
I can never find her.

567
00:50:17.600 --> 00:50:25.790
That's why the fact that Anna is in Korea
now feels like a death sentence to me.

568
00:50:29.120 --> 00:50:33.890
And that's why you shouldn't
have brought me here.

569
00:50:39.330 --> 00:50:42.990
But there's no use in
crying over spilled milk.

570
00:50:45.040 --> 00:50:46.890
You better keep your promise.

571
00:50:47.880 --> 00:50:49.290
I'm begging you.

572
00:50:57.190 --> 00:50:59.940
All right. Let's go.

573
00:51:00.790 --> 00:51:08.290
To make my poor daughter even sadder.

574
00:51:17.890 --> 00:51:20.500
What's going on. Assemblyman?

575
00:51:20.500 --> 00:51:22.790
I heard that Anna is here right now.

576
00:51:22.790 --> 00:51:23.790
What?

577
00:51:24.600 --> 00:51:25.890
Oh. yes.

578
00:51:34.690 --> 00:51:36.790
Assemblyman Jang is going
to the infirmary?

579
00:51:36.790 --> 00:51:39.000
All right.

580
00:51:41.390 --> 00:51:43.000
Mirror.

581
00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:45.690
Show me the CCTV feed from
the room that Anna is in.

582
00:51:47.714 --> 00:51:59.714
Subtitles by DramaFever
Synced by NChoerunnisa

583
00:52:00.690 --> 00:52:04.100
Anna. Your dad is here.

584
00:52:06.500 --> 00:52:07.790
Is she asleep?

585
00:52:07.790 --> 00:52:09.890
Um. no. Not yet.

586
00:52:09.890 --> 00:52:12.290
Oh no.

587
00:52:12.290 --> 00:52:16.100
I guess Anna is mad at me. then.

588
00:52:16.100 --> 00:52:21.000
Geez. I'm sorry. Anna.

589
00:52:21.000 --> 00:52:25.390
I was so busy up until now.

590
00:52:26.500 --> 00:52:30.190
What kind of illness does she have.
though? Why is she still here?

591
00:52:31.100 --> 00:52:34.390
Well. she ate strawberry
ice cream. and...

592
00:52:34.390 --> 00:52:36.550
Strawberry ice cream?
Well. so what?

593
00:52:36.550 --> 00:52:37.550
What?

594
00:52:38.940 --> 00:52:41.690
Well. um. Young Miss
has a strawberry allergy. so...

595
00:52:41.690 --> 00:52:46.290
What? She's allergic to strawberries?

596
00:52:48.290 --> 00:52:51.890
Oh no.

597
00:52:51.890 --> 00:52:57.000
You should've been careful!
Why did you feed her such a thing?

598
00:53:01.290 --> 00:53:07.500
Anna... did it hurt a lot. honey?

599
00:53:15.290 --> 00:53:21.000
He's her dad. and yet he didn't
even know about her allergy?

600
00:53:22.290 --> 00:53:27.690
Can all of you leave?
I want to talk to her alone.

601
00:53:27.690 --> 00:53:28.890
Yes. sir.

602
00:53:55.500 --> 00:53:57.190
Anna.

603
00:53:58.000 --> 00:54:00.000
Nobody is here now.

604
00:54:00.690 --> 00:54:04.890
So let's talk a bit with Daddy. okay?

605
00:54:28.100 --> 00:54:29.890
Dad!

606
00:54:31.890 --> 00:54:33.640
Dad!

607
00:54:36.290 --> 00:54:39.890
That's right.
Yes. Anna.

608
00:54:43.100 --> 00:54:46.690
Oh. my daughter.

609
00:54:51.290 --> 00:54:54.390
<i>I'm sorry. Anna.</i>

610
00:54:56.390 --> 00:54:58.690
I missed you so much. Dad!

611
00:54:58.690 --> 00:55:00.000
Oh. yes.

612
00:55:04.690 --> 00:55:11.600
Yes. I missed you too. Anna.

613
00:55:22.190 --> 00:55:24.500
All right. let's look here.

614
00:55:26.100 --> 00:55:28.290
Oh my.

615
00:55:28.290 --> 00:55:31.500
Looks my daughter is
all grown up now.

616
00:55:32.890 --> 00:55:35.000
You could probably even
get married now.

617
00:55:39.100 --> 00:55:40.660
Yes. Anna.

618
00:55:41.890 --> 00:55:43.790
Wait just a bit longer.

619
00:55:43.790 --> 00:55:48.000
When I become president.
I'll choose a fine guy for you.

620
00:55:48.000 --> 00:55:51.690
You'll be able to go on dates
and meet up with friends.

621
00:55:51.690 --> 00:55:53.100
You'll have a fun life.

622
00:55:53.100 --> 00:55:57.390
And when the time comes.
I'll let you get married.

623
00:55:58.140 --> 00:56:02.600
So you don't need to
worry about anything anymore.

624
00:56:02.600 --> 00:56:04.600
Okay?

625
00:56:04.600 --> 00:56:06.890
Dad. please listen to me.

626
00:56:06.890 --> 00:56:09.390
Mom didn't commit suicide.

627
00:56:09.390 --> 00:56:12.000
I remembered everything that
happened that night.

628
00:56:12.000 --> 00:56:15.190
<i>When I'd gone into Mom's room.
she was already passed out.</i>

629
00:56:15.890 --> 00:56:21.000
<i>And someone covered my eyes
so that I couldn't see who they were</i>

630
00:56:21.000 --> 00:56:22.690
and my mouth too.

631
00:56:24.390 --> 00:56:25.890
Anna.

632
00:56:26.390 --> 00:56:29.190
All of that is in the past now.

633
00:56:29.890 --> 00:56:31.690
You must forget about it now.

634
00:56:31.690 --> 00:56:33.890
It's true. Dad!

635
00:56:33.890 --> 00:56:36.890
And that woman came in.

636
00:56:36.890 --> 00:56:40.690
Choi Yoo Jin definitely killed Mom.

637
00:56:40.690 --> 00:56:42.000
Anna!

638
00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:44.290
You shouldn't just
say things like that.

639
00:56:44.290 --> 00:56:45.290
Dad.

640
00:56:45.290 --> 00:56:46.890
Don't ever say anything
like that ever again.

641
00:56:46.890 --> 00:56:52.000
If anyone hears you say that.
it'll just get in my way

642
00:56:52.000 --> 00:56:54.000
and it'll be bad for you too.

643
00:56:55.690 --> 00:56:57.390
Anna.

644
00:56:57.390 --> 00:56:59.000
You're just imagining all that

645
00:56:59.000 --> 00:57:03.890
because you experienced something
traumatizing at a young age.

646
00:57:03.890 --> 00:57:05.690
No. Dad.

647
00:57:05.690 --> 00:57:09.290
Mom cried a lot that day. so
I did give her that medicine. but...

648
00:57:09.290 --> 00:57:10.690
Anna!

649
00:57:11.190 --> 00:57:13.190
Are you really going
to be like this?

650
00:57:13.190 --> 00:57:17.000
Are you doing this because you
want to see your dad fail?

651
00:57:17.500 --> 00:57:18.500
Dad.

652
00:57:18.500 --> 00:57:23.190
If you say anything like that again.
I'll never see you again.

653
00:57:24.600 --> 00:57:26.290
Are you okay with that?

654
00:57:26.790 --> 00:57:28.290
Dad.

655
00:57:30.690 --> 00:57:35.890
Yes. You're a good girl.

656
00:57:38.000 --> 00:57:42.690
Yes. That's how you should be.

657
00:57:46.790 --> 00:57:48.600
<i>I'm sorry. Anna.</i>

658
00:57:49.600 --> 00:57:51.790
<i>Wait just a bit longer. please.</i>

659
00:58:10.280 --> 00:58:12.500
There's something that
I want to ask you. Dad.

660
00:58:12.500 --> 00:58:15.000
Yes? What is it?

661
00:58:16.690 --> 00:58:18.790
Did you love Mom?

662
00:58:19.290 --> 00:58:20.600
What?

663
00:58:25.890 --> 00:58:28.690
Of course I did.

664
00:58:28.690 --> 00:58:31.000
That's why you were born.

665
00:58:31.000 --> 00:58:36.500
And did Mom really use
me to blackmail you?

666
00:58:37.000 --> 00:58:38.190
What?

667
00:58:43.390 --> 00:58:48.000
<i>Choi Yoo Jin.
You devil.</i>

668
00:58:49.690 --> 00:58:52.500
Is that why you threw
me and Mom away?

669
00:59:06.100 --> 00:59:07.500
Anna.

670
00:59:08.690 --> 00:59:12.390
Those are adult matters.

671
00:59:12.390 --> 00:59:17.100
I'm an adult now too.
And I want to know.

672
00:59:17.100 --> 00:59:18.290
Anna.

673
00:59:18.290 --> 00:59:22.100
None of that matters anymore.

674
00:59:23.600 --> 00:59:25.000
Why?

675
00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:28.000
You said you loved Mom. though.

676
00:59:28.000 --> 00:59:30.190
But Mom died!

677
00:59:30.890 --> 00:59:36.100
And I was forced to go abroad. but
you didn't even come to look for me!

678
00:59:36.100 --> 00:59:39.000
So why is that meaningless?

679
00:59:47.500 --> 00:59:48.790
Anna.

680
00:59:49.690 --> 00:59:54.690
Your dad is someone who's doing
important things for this country.

681
00:59:54.690 --> 00:59:57.000
And when you do
important things like I do...

682
00:59:57.690 --> 01:00:01.100
matters that are less significant
fall to the wayside.

683
01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:11.690
So it was true.

684
01:00:11.690 --> 01:00:13.290
What do you mean?

685
01:00:14.500 --> 01:00:19.600
<i>I'm sure you thought that
you were all your dad had left</i>

686
01:00:19.600 --> 01:00:22.920
but you don't mean that much to him.

687
01:00:22.920 --> 01:00:28.290
You're just a small. burdensome
fragment of his past.

688
01:00:28.290 --> 01:00:31.190
What Choi Yoo Jin
told me was true.

689
01:00:35.690 --> 01:00:37.890
It's a vana ilusiÃ³n
(FUTILE DREAM).

690
01:00:56.640 --> 01:00:57.890
Anna.

691
01:01:05.790 --> 01:01:09.690
Yes. I'm sure you must
be quite tired today.

692
01:01:09.690 --> 01:01:12.190
It'd be best for you
to get some sleep.

693
01:01:12.790 --> 01:01:17.190
Also. don't think about
unnecessary things anymore

694
01:01:17.190 --> 01:01:19.390
and keep yourself healthy.

695
01:01:21.840 --> 01:01:28.390
I... I'll come by
often from now on.

696
01:01:28.390 --> 01:01:29.690
Okay?

697
01:02:15.690 --> 01:02:23.500
<i>To think that I hinged
my fate on scum like you.</i>

698
01:03:40.310 --> 01:03:52.310
Subtitles by DramaFever
Synced by NChoerunnisa

699
01:03:53.290 --> 01:03:56.290
<i>Please investigate him
in a strict. impartial way.</i>

700
01:03:56.290 --> 01:03:58.130
<i>I'll have to pull out the blade first.</i>

701
01:03:58.130 --> 01:03:59.450
<i>Why did you bring Dad here?</i>

702
01:03:59.450 --> 01:04:01.190
<i>Because I don't want you to die.</i>

703
01:04:02.220 --> 01:04:05.290
<i>Standing by as close to
the target as possible.</i>

704
01:04:05.290 --> 01:04:08.290
<i>My father is...</i>

705
01:04:08.290 --> 01:04:09.310
<i>No.</i>

706
01:04:09.310 --> 01:04:12.100
<i>Anna is in your hands now.</i>

707
01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:14.000
<i>I'll protect you from now on.</i>

708
01:04:14.000 --> 01:04:17.890
<i>I'll make it so that nobody will ever
be able to touch you again.</i>

709
01:04:18.690 --> 01:04:20.100
<i>Thanks.</i>

